```

Additionally, you should handle the case when the array is empty (i.e., `start > end`). In this case, your function should return a special value, such as `INT_MIN`, to indicate that there is no maximum element.

The input array will have a maximum length of 10^6 elements.

Here is an example of how the function should be used:
```cpp
int arr[] = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
