Please write a function in Java to sort a given array of integers into ascending order using a merge sort algorithm. The function should have the following signature:
void mergeSort(int[] array, int low, int high)

The function should sort the elements in the array from index low to index high (inclusive) using the merge sort algorithm. The merge sort algorithm works as follows:

1. Divide the array into two halves, called left and right.
2. Recursively sort the left half of the array.
3. Recursively sort the right half of the array.
4. Merge the sorted left and right halves into a single sorted array.

Note: The merge step should be implemented using an auxiliary array to minimize memory usage. The merge operation should be performed in-place, meaning that the original array should be modified directly without creating a new array.

Example:
int[] array = {9, 5, 2, 7, 1, 8};
mergeSort(array, 0, array.length - 1);
// The array should be sorted in ascending order: {1, 2, 5, 7, 8, 9}

Please write the code for the mergeSort function.

output:
```
public class MergeSort {

  public static void mergeSort(int[] array, int low, int high) {
    if (low < high) {
      int mid = (low + high) / 2;
      mergeSort(array, low, mid);
      mergeSort(array, mid + 1, high);
      merge(array, low, mid, high);
    }
  }

  private static void merge(int[] array, int low, int mid, int high) {
    int[] temp = new int[high - low + 1];
    int i = low;
    int j = mid + 1;
    int k = 0;

    while (i <= mid && j <= high) {
      if (array[i] <= array[j]) {
        temp[k++] = array[i++];
      } else {
        temp[k++] = array[j++];
      }
    }

    while (i <= mid) {
      temp[k++] = array[i++];
    }

    while (j <= high) {
      temp[k++] = array[j++];
    }

    for (int x = low; x <= high; x++) {
      array[x] = temp[x - low];
    }
  }

  public static void main(String[] args) {
    int[] array = {9, 5, 2, 7, 1, 8};
    mergeSort(array, 0, array.length - 1);
    for (int i = 0; i < array.length; i++) {
      System.out.print(array[i] + " ");
    }
  }
}
```

